---
title: Moroccan Beef Tagine with Currant Cauli-Rice & Roasted Veggies
description: Take a little bit of ras el hanout, some flavoursome beef mince and a sprinkling of currants for sweetness, and what have you
got? Why, it’s the perfect recipe for a delicious beef tagine. Except we've added a welcome twist by replacing couscous with
cauliflower rice. Now have at it!

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 30g carbohydrates per serving.*
